2026-05-17 21:34:05 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #5 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"code": "# intent: Compute difference in bacterial exceedance rates for 2023 marine beach samples\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom io import StringIO\n\n# Load CSVs from s3 via their s3_uri using pandas read_csv directly (execute_ideal supports)\npop_uri = 's3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-environment-hard-7/files/environmental-justice-populations.csv'\ntest_uri = 's3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-environment-hard-7/files/water-body-testing-2023.csv'\n\npop = pd.read_csv(pop_uri)\ntest = pd.read_csv(test_uri)\n\nprint('pop columns:', list(pop.columns))\nprint('test columns sample:', list(test.columns))\n\n# Normalize municipality/community naming: population file uses 'Municipality', test file uses 'Community'\n# We'll merge on exact match of names. Check how many community names match municipalities\ncommon_names = set(pop['Municipality'].str.strip().str.lower()).intersection(set(test['Community'].str.strip().str.lower()))\nprint('common name count:', len(common_names))\n\n# Prepare population groups\npop['Pct_EJ_Pop'] = pd.to_numeric(pop['Percent of population in EJ BGs'], errors='coerce')\nhigh_ej = pop[pop['Pct_EJ_Pop']>50].copy()\nlow_ej = pop[pop['Pct_EJ_Pop']<25].copy()\nprint('high count:', len(high_ej), 'low count:', len(low_ej))\n\n# Filter tests: Year==2023 and Beach Type Description == 'Marine'\nmarine23 = test[(test['Year']==2023) & (test['Beach Type Description'].str.strip().str.lower()=='marine')].copy()\nprint('marine23 rows:', len(marine23))\n\n# Merge by community/municipality after lowercasing\nmarine23['comm_low'] = marine23['Community'].str.strip().str.lower()\npop['mun_low'] = pop['Municipality'].str.strip().str.lower()\n\n# Tag marine23 rows as high/low/other\nhigh_set = set(high_ej['Municipality'].str.strip().str.lower())\nlow_set = set(low_ej['Municipality'].str.strip().str.lower())\n\nmarine23['ej_group'] = marine23['comm_low'].apply(lambda x: 'high' if x in high_set else ('low' if x in low_set else 'other'))\n\n# Keep only high and low\nmarine_hl = marine23[marine23['ej_group'].isin(['high','low'])].copy()\nprint('marine rows in high/low groups:', len(marine_hl))\nprint(marine_hl['ej_group'].value_counts())\n\n# Compute exceedance rates: Violation == 'Yes' counts\nmarine_hl['Violation'] = marine_hl['Violation'].astype(str)\ncounts = marine_hl.groupby('ej_group').agg(total_samples=('Violation','count'), exceedances=('Violation', lambda s: (s.str.strip().str.lower()=='yes').sum()))\ncounts['rate'] = counts['exceedances'] / counts['total_samples'] * 100\nprint(counts)\n\n# Compute difference: high - low\ndiff = counts.loc['high','rate'] - counts.loc['low','rate']\ndiff_rounded = round(diff,2)\nprint('diff_rounded:', diff_rounded)\n\n# Print final numeric value only\nprint(diff_rounded)\n", "intent": "Compute difference in exceedance rates for marine beach samples in 2023 between municipalities with >50% EJ population and <25% EJ population using provided CSVs"}) [toolUseId=call_lbGOts9CGSzVfEWdI2EITT1Y]
2026-05-17 21:34:05 | INFO | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Executing: execute_ideal({"code": "# intent: Compute difference in bacterial exceedance rates for 2023 marine beach samples\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom io import StringIO\n\n# Load CSVs from s3 via their s3_uri using pandas read_csv directly (execute_ideal supports)\npop_uri = 's3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-environment-hard-7/files/environmental-justice-populations.csv'\ntest_uri = 's3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-environment-hard-7/files/water-body-testing-2023.csv'\n\npop = pd.read_csv(pop_uri)\ntest = pd.read_csv(test_uri)\n\nprint('pop columns:', list(pop.columns))\nprint('test columns sample:', list(test.columns))\n\n# Normalize municipality/community naming: population file uses 'Municipality', test file uses 'Community'\n# We'll merge on exact match of names. Check how many community names match municipalities\ncommon_names = set(pop['Municipality'].str.strip().str.lower()).intersection(set(test['Community'].str.strip().str.lower()))\nprint('common name count:', len(common_names))\n\n# Prepare population groups\npop['Pct_EJ_Pop'] = pd.to_numeric(pop['Percent of population in EJ BGs'], errors='coerce')\nhigh_ej = pop[pop['Pct_EJ_Pop']>50].copy()\nlow_ej = pop[pop['Pct_EJ_Pop']<25].copy()\nprint('high count:', len(high_ej), 'low count:', len(low_ej))\n\n# Filter tests: Year==2023 and Beach Type Description == 'Marine'\nmarine23 = test[(test['Year']==2023) & (test['Beach Type Description'].str.strip().str.lower()=='marine')].copy()\nprint('marine23 rows:', len(marine23))\n\n# Merge by community/municipality after lowercasing\nmarine23['comm_low'] = marine23['Community'].str.strip().str.lower()\npop['mun_low'] = pop['Municipality'].str.strip().str.lower()\n\n# Tag marine23 rows as high/low/other\nhigh_set = set(high_ej['Municipality'].str.strip().str.lower())\nlow_set = set(low_ej['Municipality'].str.strip().str.lower())\n\nmarine23['ej_group'] = marine23['comm_low'].apply(lambda x: 'high' if x in high_set else ('low' if x in low_set else 'other'))\n\n# Keep only high and low\nmarine_hl = marine23[marine23['ej_group'].isin(['high','low'])].copy()\nprint('marine rows in high/low groups:', len(marine_hl))\nprint(marine_hl['ej_group'].value_counts())\n\n# Compute exceedance rates: Violation == 'Yes' counts\nmarine_hl['Violation'] = marine_hl['Violation'].astype(str)\ncounts = marine_hl.groupby('ej_group').agg(total_samples=('Violation','count'), exceedances=('Violation', lambda s: (s.str.strip().str.lower()=='yes').sum()))\ncounts['rate'] = counts['exceedances'] / counts['total_samples'] * 100\nprint(counts)\n\n# Compute difference: high - low\ndiff = counts.loc['high','rate'] - counts.loc['low','rate']\ndiff_rounded = round(diff,2)\nprint('diff_rounded:', diff_rounded)\n\n# Print final numeric value only\nprint(diff_rounded)\n", "intent": "Compute difference in exceedance rates for marine beach samples in 2023 between municipalities with >50% EJ population and <25% EJ population using provided CSVs"})
